pr_review_comment_body:
Consider using `symfit.core.support.cache` to remove the boilerplate in checking for `_initial_guesses`. This way you also don't have to do `self._initial_guesses = None`. Adding the setter still works with this since you modify the `cache`.

Use as 
```python
@property
@cache
def initial_guesses(self):
    return [p.value for p in self.params]
```

The nested conditionals here get a bit hard to read. How about this:

```python
    def __str__(self):
        if not self.done():
            return self.job_status()

        if not self.report:
            return '%s - loss: %f' % (self.name(), self.loss)
        
        s = '%s - WER: %f, loss: %s, accuracy: %f' % (self.name(), self.wer, self.loss, self.accuracy)
        if len(self.samples) > 0:
            line = '\n' + ('-' * 80)
            for sample in self.samples:
                s += line + '\n' + str(sample)
            s += line
        return s
```

